page.title: 04TEBAY NEWS STORIES JUNE 1985
page.content:
News Stories "WESTMORLAND GAZETTE" {BOY BITTEN BY ADDER}Paul Davies 16 in intensive care for 24 hours after being bitten while fishing near Newby Bridge. {BODY ON RAILWAY LINE}Woman's body on Carlisle/Preston line Tues 11 June. {BODY AT BRIGSTEER}Body of restaurant manager found in woods Monday 10 June. {HELICOPTER PROBLEMS}Due to complaints from people in Ambleside planned flights during the summer are having to be moved to Keswick.Noise was the main worry & disturbance to walkers on the fells. {POSTMAN PAT IN CUMBRIA}This popular childrens character from TV & books was at Levens Hall for an event for the disabled & handicapped organised by the local Lions Clubs
(Michelle Cowan/Beverley Tindall).
